HEADWORD: Hobbism
<hw>Hob"bism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The philosophical
system of <person>Thomas <etsep>Hobbes</etsep></person>, an English
materialist (1588-1679); esp., his political theory that the most
perfect form of civil government is an absolute monarchy with despotic
control over everything relating to law, morals, and religion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

